:: This trait represents a common interface for anything that allows bytes
:: to be written into it, one chunk at a time, using the `<<` operator.
::
:: The `<<` method is intended to return the same logical stream,
:: so that invocations of this method can be easily chained together.
:trait ByteStream.Writable
  :fun ref "<<"(chunk Bytes'val) @
  :fun ref push(byte U8) @
